OriginX GigShield - Complete Code Documentation

1) Project Overview
- Purpose: Parametric insurance system for delivery partners with automatic trigger-based claims.
- Core modules:
  - Frontend app (React + Vite + React Router)
  - Backend API (Node.js + Express + Mongoose)
  - AI service (`ai/`) for risk and anomaly scoring endpoints.

2) Frontend Documentation

Location: `frontend/`

Tech:
- React (Vite)
- React Router
- Custom CSS (`frontend/src/index.css`)

Main files:
- `frontend/src/App.jsx`:
  - App route setup (`/`, `/register`, `/dashboard`, `/admin`)
  - Admin route access gating via `VITE_ADMIN_ACCESS_KEY`
- `frontend/src/pages/*`: page-level UI flows (Landing, Register, Dashboard, Admin)
- `frontend/src/components/*`: shared UI components
- `frontend/vite.config.js`: React plugin + dev proxy for `/api` and `/ai`

Commands:
- `cd frontend && npm install`
- `npm run dev`
- `npm run build`
- `npm run preview`

3) Backend Documentation

Location: `backend/`

Core entry:
- `backend/server.js`
  - Middleware stack:
    - CORS
    - JSON parser
  - Route mounts:
    - `/api/auth`
    - `/api/delivery-partners`
    - `/api/insurance-policies`
    - `/api/insurance-claims`
    - `/api/disruption-events`
    - `/api/health`
  - Admin utility endpoint:
    - `POST /api/admin/trigger-weather-check`

Auth and validation:
- `backend/routes/authRoutes.js`: issues JWT token
- `backend/middleware/authMiddleware.js`: bearer token verification
- `backend/middleware/optionalAuth.js`: enforces auth only when `ENFORCE_AUTH=true`
- `backend/middleware/validationMiddleware.js`: request validation result handler
- `backend/validators/requestValidators.js`: input validation rules for partner/policy/claim endpoints

Payout wiring:
- `backend/services/paymentService.js`
  - Stub mode when payment keys are not configured
  - Live mode when payment keys are provided
- Integrated in claim/policy flows via backend services and routes

4) Database Documentation (MongoDB + Mongoose Models)

- `backend/models/DeliveryPartner.js`
  - identity/contact fields, city + coordinates, platform list, risk category, policy linkage
- `backend/models/InsurancePolicy.js`
  - plan tier, premium, max/remaining coverage, active window, status, pricing metadata, exclusions
- `backend/models/InsuranceClaim.js`
  - associated partner/policy/event, claim status, payout and fraud metadata
- `backend/models/DisruptionEvent.js`
  - disruption type, geo impact zone, measurements, exclusions, aggregate payout tracking

Database config:
- `backend/config/databaseConfig.js`
  - uses `MONGODB_URI`, fallback `mongodb://localhost:27017/gigshield`

5) API Documentation

Auth:
- `POST /api/auth/token`
  - body: `{ username, password }`
  - response: `{ accessToken, tokenType, expiresIn }`

Delivery Partner:
- `POST /api/delivery-partners/register`
- `GET /api/delivery-partners/:partnerId`

Insurance Policy:
- `POST /api/insurance-policies/subscribe`
- `GET /api/insurance-policies/partner/:partnerId`
- `GET /api/insurance-policies/:policyId`
- `PATCH /api/insurance-policies/:policyId/cancel`

Insurance Claim:
- `POST /api/insurance-claims/submit`
- `GET /api/insurance-claims/partner/:partnerId`
- `GET /api/insurance-claims/:claimId`
- `GET /api/insurance-claims/flagged`
- `PATCH /api/insurance-claims/:claimId/review`

Disruption Events:
- `POST /api/disruption-events`
- `GET /api/disruption-events`
- `POST /api/disruption-events/check-threshold`
- `POST /api/disruption-events/:eventId/trigger-claims`

Health:
- `GET /api/health`

6) Quality and CI/CD

Backend checks:
- `cd backend && npm test`

Frontend checks:
- `cd frontend && npm run build`

CI workflow (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`):
- backend: `npm ci` + `npm test`
- frontend: `npm ci` + `npm run build`

7) Deployment + Secrets Checklist

Required env vars:
- `MONGODB_URI`
- `PORT`
- `JWT_SECRET_KEY`
- `ENFORCE_AUTH`
- `AUTH_DEMO_USERNAME`
- `AUTH_DEMO_PASSWORD_HASH` (preferred) / `AUTH_DEMO_PASSWORD`
- `WEATHER_API_KEY`
- `POLLUTION_API_KEY`

Security guidance:
- Keep all secrets in environment/config stores
- Do not commit credentials to repository
- Configure CI with secret variables and minimal scope tokens

8) Feature Additions (April 2026)

This section documents the newly implemented product enhancements across Partner Dashboard, Admin Panel, and backend platform services.

8.1 High-Impact Features

A) Policy Renewal Flow (Dashboard)
- Problem addressed: no guided path when weekly policy expires.
- What was added:
  - Renewal CTA and plan picker (`basic`, `standard`, `premium`) in Dashboard when policy is missing/expired.
  - In-place renew call using existing `POST /api/insurance-policies/subscribe` flow.
- Frontend file:
  - `frontend/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx`

B) Disruption Map (Dashboard)
- Problem addressed: no visual map for disruption + partner location.
- What was added:
  - New `DisruptionMap` component to render event markers and partner marker on an India-bounds coordinate canvas.
- Frontend files:
  - `frontend/src/components/DisruptionMap.jsx`
  - `frontend/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx`

C) Real-Time Alerts (Backend SSE + Frontend Toast)
- Problem addressed: partner got no immediate notification when auto-claim is processed.
- What was added:
  - SSE alert stream service for partner-scoped live notifications.
  - New endpoint: `GET /api/alerts/stream?partnerId=<id>`
  - Auto-payout event push from claim processing service when payout is processed.
  - Dashboard subscribes via EventSource and shows live toasts.
- Backend files:
  - `backend/services/alertStreamService.js`
  - `backend/server.js`
  - `backend/services/claimProcessingService.js`
- Frontend files:
  - `frontend/src/api/rakshaRideApi.js`
  - `frontend/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx`

D) One-Click Demo Seeder (Admin)
- Problem addressed: no instant end-to-end demo flow for judges.
- What was added:
  - Admin endpoint to seed partner + policy + event + triggered claim.
  - New endpoint: `POST /api/admin/seed-demo`
  - Admin UI action button to call seeder and refresh data.
- Backend file:
  - `backend/server.js`
- Frontend files:
  - `frontend/src/api/rakshaRideApi.js`
  - `frontend/src/pages/Admin.jsx`

E) Claim Confidence Explanation (Dashboard)
- Problem addressed: anomaly notes existed but were not visible in UI.
- What was added:
  - Claim verification/fraud notes now persisted for both auto-approved and flagged claims.
  - Dashboard table now parses and displays compact anomaly/confidence notes.
- Backend file:
  - `backend/services/claimProcessingService.js`
- Frontend file:
  - `frontend/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx`

